--
-- demo\theGUI\hText.exw
-- =====================
--
--  Experimental. A planned drop-in canva-based replacement for gText.
--
--  Note the frankly rubbish single-step Ctrl Z toggle of the native control
--  has been replaced with a hopefully much better stack, with Ctrl Z being
--  strictly undo, and (the natively ignored) Ctrl Y being strictly redo.
--
--  Of course it is utterly, utterly insane to do it this way, but quite a
--  bit of fun and extremely pleasing to prove to myself that I got the base
--  API right, while (re-)implementing an equally elegant higher level API.
--
--  On the other hand, once you have a text field working, you can start to
--  think about tweaking it to support a spin field, and (later) maybe even 
--  a dropdown and datepick, rather than start from scratch &/or duplicate 
--  ~700 lines, along with however many bugs they might contain.
--
--  This code may also have uses elsewhere, for instance should you hanker
--  after in-place editing on a gTable this should contain almost all the 
--  code you need, except perhaps for some finer positioning points, with
--  potential re-use/re-draw of the gTable's canvas all down to you.
--
--  Differences to native (semi-deliberate):
--   Does not switch mouse cursor from ARROW to TEXT when it moves over the field.
--  Differences to GTK native (semi-deliberate):
--   Does not implement the truly awful auto-full-select on *EVERY* (re-)focus.
--
--  Aside: I never did get the native GtkEntry to expand horizontally, not
--          that I tried very hard to do so.
--  In truth I have imitated the GTK2/3 look and feel just to show that I can,
--          but certainly not because I think it is a spectacularly good idea!
--
-- enum TEXT, SPIN, CHECKBOX, DATEPICK
-- constant ?? = TEXT
--/*
--        SPIN
--          (non inheritable, creation only) Makes the control a <a href="gSpin.htm">gSpin</a>. Can be <a href="logicops.htm#tf">false</a> (the default),
--          <a href="logicops.htm#tf">true</a> (== {0,100,1,false}), or {lo,hi[,step[,wrap]]} where lo and hi must be integers with lo&lt;=hi,
--          step must be an integer&gt;=1, and wrap must be true/false. Reading ths attribute yeilds either false or a four-element sequence. 
--          Setting before the first display defaults the control size from lo/hi. Changing the <a href="gSetAttribute.htm#FONT">FONT</a>
--          changes the up/down image sizes to match.
--*/

puts(1,"")
